# Deployment repository

The user runs, builds, and deploys OpsBlaze from the sibling **`~/opsblaze`** checkout, not from this workspace (`opsblaze-1`).

- Treat **`~/opsblaze`** as the live app: build, restart, logs, and status checks go there.
- This workspace (`opsblaze-1`) is the development copy; after meaningful changes, sync to `~/opsblaze` and rebuild/restart there.
- Use `node bin/opsblaze.cjs` in **`~/opsblaze`** for server lifecycle (see process-management rule).
- Do not assume the user sees UI or server changes until they are synced to `~/opsblaze` and the app is restarted.

Sync pattern (run from this workspace root):

```bash
rsync -a --exclude node_modules --exclude dist --exclude data --exclude .git \
  ./src/ ~/opsblaze/src/
rsync -a --exclude node_modules \
  ./server/ ~/opsblaze/server/
cd ~/opsblaze && npm run build && node bin/opsblaze.cjs restart
```

Also sync `package.json`, `package-lock.json`, `.env.example`, and test config when dependencies or env vars change.
